Reasoning: The paper deals with the problem of querying the most probable state configuration of some of the network variables given evidence in Bayesian networks. This problem is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), data structures (cs.DS), data mining (cs.DM), and computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper presents new results and algorithms for this problem, which are likely to be of interest to researchers in these sub-fields.
